               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160710-30-person251">
                  JOHN 
                  WALLIS
               <interp inst="t18160710-30-person251" type="surname" value="WALLIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160710-30-person251" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160710-30-person251" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the night of the 3rd of June, about eleven o'clock, I was in the Cooper's Arms public house; being fatigued, I felt a sleep. When I awoke, my hat and pocket-book were gone.</p>

               <p>JASSE TAYLOR. I am servant at the Cooper's Arms. The prisoner at the bat was the only man who was in that room beside the prosecutor. The hat was lying on the table, and after the prisoner was gone, the hat was missing.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160710-30-person252">
                  DAVID 
                  YOUNG
               <interp inst="t18160710-30-person252" type="surname" value="YOUNG"></interp>
